cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SD, cs.CE, cs.SOC

This paper analyzes correlations and causalities between Bitcoin market indicators and Twitter posts containing emotional signals on Bitcoin. The paper uses data analysis techniques to study the relationship between Twitter signals and Bitcoin market values. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Other likely sub-categories include cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.SD (Software Development), cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), and cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks).
